IMPORTANT:

- Minimize tool calls.
- Read multiple files at once instead of one file at a time.
- Do not repeatedly scan the same directories.
- Do not execute exploratory commands unless necessary.
- Before running another command, determine whether existing context is sufficient.
- If a command fails because of shell compatibility, do not retry similar commands repeatedly.
- Batch operations whenever possible.
- Wait for user approval before performing more than 3 tool calls in sequence.